# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Caddy reverse proxy for the Palworld Server Manager web UI (HTTPS via DuckDNS)
#
# Replace YOURDOMAIN with your DuckDNS subdomain and 8080 with your WEB_PORT.
# Use ONE of the two server blocks below.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ── Option A (RECOMMENDED): DNS-01 challenge ─────────────────────────────────
# Works behind NAT and does NOT require forwarding port 80 — only port 443.
# Requires a Caddy build that includes the DuckDNS DNS module:
#   xcaddy build --with github.com/caddy-dns/duckdns
# or download "Caddy with plugins" and tick the `duckdns` provider at:
#   https://caddyserver.com/download
# Set the DUCKDNS_TOKEN environment variable for the Caddy process before running.
#
YOURDOMAIN.duckdns.org {
	tls {
		dns duckdns {env.DUCKDNS_TOKEN}
	}
	encode gzip
	reverse_proxy 127.0.0.1:8080
}

# ── Option B: HTTP-01 challenge (stock Caddy binary) ─────────────────────────
# No custom build needed, but you MUST forward BOTH port 80 and port 443 on your
# router to this machine. Delete Option A above and uncomment this block to use it.
#
# YOURDOMAIN.duckdns.org {
# 	encode gzip
# 	reverse_proxy 127.0.0.1:8080
# }

# Notes:
# - Caddy flushes Server-Sent Events correctly by default (no buffering config needed).
# - Never expose the Palworld REST API port (8212) or the game ports through Caddy.
